{"id":"lumen-r5i","title":"Phase 1 — Foundations \u0026 Basic Markdown Editor (MVP)","description":"A fast, native, calm plain-Markdown editor for the Lumen vault app. Open a folder as a vault, browse files in a sidebar, open/edit/save .md reliably; dark-by-default UI with tabs + slim status bar. Stands up the SPM workspace, data model, and architecture later phases extend. Source of truth = files; SQLite index is a rebuildable cache (deleting .lumen/ must never lose notes). OUT OF SCOPE (Phase 2-3): live preview/WYSIWYG, tree-sitter, wikilinks/backlinks, graph, command palette, global search UI, AI. TARGET: macOS 26 \"Tahoe\" min, Swift 6.2 strict/approachable concurrency, Xcode 26, TextKit 2; Liquid Glass chrome. DoD: open folder→see .md→open several tabs→edit+save→relaunch restores state; clean external edits auto-reload, edits-under-unsaved prompt before overwrite; dark/light/system+accent work; sub-second cold launch + no perceptible typing latency on a large synthetic vault; SPM workspace + 4 core packages + notes index + CI in place.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"epic","owner":"adam@example.com","created_at":"2026-06-03T04:33:59Z","created_by":"Adam","updated_at":"2026-06-03T04:33:59Z","labels":["phase-1-mvp"],"dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
